p: Protein content is determined by the presence of amino acids, nectar sources, enzymes secreted from honey bees and storage conditions [ 30]. Manuka honey exhibited the highest protein content (128.5 mg/100 g) as this honey is categorized as “high protein” compared to other natural commercial honeys [ 43]. The four other honeys contain lower protein contents than manuka, varying from 111.4 for jiaogulan honey to 66.6, 55.3 and 25.6 (mg/100 g) for olive, guggul, and arjuna honey, respectively.
